lead_paragraph: Striker Luuk de Jong returned from suspension to help PSV Eindhoven beat ADO Den Haag 2-0 and extend their lead on top of the Dutch league on Saturday.    Marco van Ginkel netted the opening goal and the league's top scorer De Jong, who missed PSV’s midweek draw with Atletico Madrid in the Champions League, struck the second as PSV secured victory to provisionally move four points clear of Ajax Amsterdam.

headline.print_headline: De Jong Returns From Suspension to Help PSV Extend Lead
